genresAdvancedInfo.name: palestinian traditional
genresAdvancedInfo.description: Palestinian traditional music is deeply rooted in the country's rich cultural heritage, featuring instruments such as the oud, qanun, and darbuka. It is often performed at weddings, festivals, and other celebrations, and reflects the diversity of Palestinian culture through its various regional styles. Notable artists in this genre include Le Trio Joubran, Sabreen, and Rim Banna.
